parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes vibrate or pulse
the ABS light comes on
the brakes release on rough roads
the brakes fail in reverse
the brakes make a grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the brakes vibrate or pulse
the brakes release on rough roads
the brakes fail in reverse
the brakes make a grinding sound
the vehicle shakes or vibrates when applying the brakes
the brakes have extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the brake pedal can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the front end suspension to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Excessive tire wear
suspension clunking noise
sudden collapse of the front end suspension
difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear springs can cause excessive wear on the front tires, leading to reduced traction and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Excessive wear on the front tires
uneven tire wear
noise from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower control arm can cause the wheel to fall off, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Noise from the front of the vehicle
wheel separation from the upper control arm
difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of incorrect balancing gear can cause damage to the unit, leading to premature wear and failure of other components.
symptoms: Vibration
noise
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Incompatible Seat Belts with Child Safety Seats
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability of seat belts to accommodate child safety seats can compromise the safety of children in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Seat belts do not fit around child safety seats
making it difficult or impossible to securely fasten the child seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Jammed or malfunctioning seat belts can prevent occupants from being properly restrained, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belts jam or become twisted
preventing proper use; seat belts do not retract properly
becoming stuck or loose; seat belts become tangled.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Broken or Faulty Seat Belt Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken or faulty seat belt components can prevent occupants from being properly restrained, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Rear seat lap/shoulder bolts break
preventing the seat belt from being fastened.
